7_Temporal_Difference_Learning
3rd method to solve MDP
TD is Fully On-Line... Don't need full episode
Just like DP and MC



Not calculating full Return (G)
Recursive definition of V
Update V(s) as soon as we know s'
Estimate G
No Model Required
No Full Episode Required

Need state AND action
Need exploration... we choose epsilon-greedy
SARSA on-policy finds higher value Q(s,a) than Q-Learning, but finds a less optimum path
(from Youtube talk)

epsilon can be 1/t, 0.5/t, etc.
can also be 1/t^0.5, or 1/t^2, etc.
Decaying Learning Rate is problematic
Let learning rate decay by Count on Q(s,a)
Each Q(s,a) will have its own learning rate
Since updates are done On-Line, there is no play_game routine
Deviates from earlier strategy
Q-Learning is OFF-POLICY... actions can be random

Episodes have longer run times
Yes... if policy used in Q-Learning is greedy
